This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image deconvolution for fluorescence microscopy. The use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.MM) and deep learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the development of a new method for image restoration, which could fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the use of neural networks for image processing could also place this paper in the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
